WEBVTT



00:00:00.736 --> 00:00:04.576
Friends, welcome to Word on Fire Catholic Ministries.

00:00:04.384 --> 00:00:09.856
Word on Fire is an apostolate dedicated to the mission of evangelization.

00:00:09.568 --> 00:00:15.040
Using media both old and new to share the faith on every continent,

00:00:14.752 --> 00:00:18.784
and to facilitate an encounter with Christ and His Church.

00:00:18.816 --> 00:00:27.040
The efforts of Word on Fire engage the culture and bring the transformative power of God's Word where it is most needed.

00:00:27.040 --> 00:00:36.448
Today, we invite you to join Bishop Robert Barron as he preaches the Gospel and shares the warmth and light of Christ with each one of us.

00:00:39.456 --> 00:00:48.416
Peace be with you. Friends, we come to this wonderful feast of the Ascension of the Lord. We have this feast right at the end of the Easter season as a prelude to Jesus.

00:00:48.128 --> 00:00:58.176
1 Peter 1, verse 12. And getting the ascension of the Lord right is very important for understanding many aspects of the church's

00:00:57.696 --> 00:01:01.984
100% church's life. And so I want to dwell on that a little bit with you today.

00:01:01.760 --> 00:01:02.880
um, ah,

00:01:02.528 --> 00:01:09.792
I want to do so under two headings. The first, I'm going to call more political. The second, I'm going to call more liturgical.

00:01:10.048 --> 00:01:15.488
They are both hinted at in the great statement in the creed that we recite week after week.

00:01:15.200 --> 00:01:18.112
He ascended into heaven.

00:01:18.240 --> 00:01:19.968
And is seated

00:01:19.712 --> 00:01:22.144
at the right hand of the Father.

00:01:22.240 --> 00:01:25.152
So every week we say that as part of the Nicene Creed.

00:01:25.088 --> 00:01:28.608
He ascended into heaven and is seated at the top of the mountain.

00:01:28.384 --> 00:01:30.400
At the right hand of the Father.

00:01:30.400 --> 00:01:32.448
What does that mean?

00:01:32.960 --> 00:01:37.120
Well, first of all, and I've made this point with you before, but it's worth making again.

00:01:37.376 --> 00:01:44.768
The ascension of the Lord does not mean his translation to another place within the cosmos.

00:01:44.832 --> 00:01:52.864
So think of Jesus moving from Capernaum to Jerusalem. He's moving from point A to point B within the space-time continuum.

00:01:53.216 --> 00:01:59.712
If we think of the ascension as Jesus simply like taking off like a rocket and going up into space,

00:01:59.712 --> 00:02:06.848
Well, heck, even if he's moving at the speed of light in 2,000 years, he'd still be within the confines of the Milky Way galaxy.

00:02:06.848 --> 00:02:14.880
It doesn't mean he's moving. Something as trivial as moving from one place to another within the universe.

00:02:14.816 --> 00:02:16.288
Rather this,

00:02:17.056 --> 00:02:20.096
It's the transition of Jesus from

00:02:19.936 --> 00:02:22.080
This dimensional system

00:02:22.272 --> 00:02:27.360
to the higher dimensional system that the Bible calls heaven.

00:02:27.360 --> 00:02:32.640
Now, when you see heaven or the clouds or the heavens, that's a symbol, right?

00:02:32.352 --> 00:02:37.408
So we point to the sky as an evocation of something that is eternal.

00:02:37.280 --> 00:02:38.752
Beyond. Beyond.

00:02:38.816 --> 00:02:43.680
Our ordinary experience beyond the confines of this world.

00:02:44.096 --> 00:02:47.136
We're speaking of the dimension of God.

00:02:47.584 --> 00:02:49.184
And I'll think for a minute, everybody.

00:02:49.120 --> 00:02:52.576
God is not an item within the universe.

00:02:52.832 --> 00:03:02.880
The mistake that atheists old and new make over and over again is they think of God as a big being within the context of the universe. And then they look around for him. Some say he's here.

00:03:02.400 --> 00:03:06.688
Some say he's here. Some say he's not. But it's getting the whole thing wrong. Right.

00:03:06.688 --> 00:03:08.480
The creator.

00:03:08.544 --> 00:03:14.432
20% of the time-space continuum is not an item within the time-space continuum.

00:03:14.496 --> 00:03:20.000
We say that God is beyond space and beyond time.

00:03:20.064 --> 00:03:25.248
So God's eternity, for example, read Thomas Aquinas on this, doesn't mean that God

00:03:25.024 --> 00:03:35.072
It lives in everlasting time like a vampire who never fades away. It means God exists in a manner that is transcendent to time. Now, here's an example.

00:03:34.592 --> 00:03:35.904
Here's an important point.

00:03:36.640 --> 00:03:42.272
This doesn't make God irrelevant to our experience. On the contrary, it makes God

00:03:42.304 --> 00:03:43.616
More

00:03:43.456 --> 00:03:51.808
present to it, more available to the totality of it. The eternal God, who is beyond time, yes,

00:03:51.680 --> 00:03:54.336
Presses upon every moment of time.

00:03:54.720 --> 00:03:57.696
God, who's beyond space, yes.

00:03:57.600 --> 00:04:00.192
It is present to every and all.

00:04:00.384 --> 00:04:01.632
Place

00:04:02.368 --> 00:04:08.640
Now, I've used this image before, but I've always found it very useful to understand this kind of paradox.

00:04:08.960 --> 00:04:10.464
You think of a

00:04:10.240 --> 00:04:12.896
Square on a two-dimensional plane.

00:04:13.184 --> 00:04:14.208
Now,

00:04:14.560 --> 00:04:18.880
Move to a higher dimension, move to a three-dimensional system.

00:04:18.688 --> 00:04:26.496
and the square becomes like a cube. Now a cube can fit in it, so to speak, an infinite number of squares.

00:04:26.496 --> 00:04:30.272
It can be present to an infinity of squares.

00:04:30.688 --> 00:04:34.784
Because it exists at a level transcendent to the two dimensions.

00:04:34.464 --> 00:04:42.784
Think of a circle in relation to a sphere in three dimensions. The sphere can contain an infinite number of circles.

00:04:43.040 --> 00:04:44.640
In a similar way.

00:04:44.896 --> 00:04:49.568
God's dimension, which is beyond space and beyond time,

00:04:49.504 --> 00:04:51.488
It can be present.

00:04:51.968 --> 00:04:55.552
To every space and to every moment of time.

00:04:55.904 --> 00:05:05.952
That's the paradox, but so much of the life of the church depends upon this. So the ascension of the Lord means that Jesus, who operated indeed within our time,

00:05:05.472 --> 00:05:07.424
In our time-space continuum, we have

00:05:07.168 --> 00:05:13.664
I can pinpoint, you know, around 2,000 years ago in ancient Palestine, that's where Jesus was.

00:05:13.856 --> 00:05:19.744
But the ascended Christ now has entered into the divine dimension in such a way

00:05:20.032 --> 00:05:23.264
that he can indeed impinge upon

00:05:23.264 --> 00:05:26.048
All of space and all of time.

00:05:26.336 --> 00:05:35.072
I'll give you an example. This morning, I'm in my chapel praying my holy hour, and I was doing the Jesus Prayer. You know, Lord Jesus Christ, I'm believing God, have mercy on me, a sinner

00:05:35.488 --> 00:05:42.528
I wasn't just remembering some figure from long ago. I wasn't engaging in some subjective fantasy.

00:05:42.304 --> 00:05:45.600
No, I was in dialogue with Jesus.

00:05:45.984 --> 00:05:48.288
And that's why people all over the world,

00:05:48.128 --> 00:05:51.264
It can be praying at the same time to the same Jesus. Amen.

00:05:51.232 --> 00:05:53.600
Because now ascended

00:05:53.408 --> 00:05:56.416
He can be present to every and all moment.

00:05:56.416 --> 00:05:57.824
Of time and space.

00:05:58.080 --> 00:06:04.000
Okay. Now, let's pursue this with what I'm calling the political interpretation of mind. Okay.

00:06:04.960 --> 00:06:07.200
This ascended Christ

